1H Pass 2D Pass 2NT Pass 3NT Pass Pass Pass
{After South's 1\H opening North counts 12 HCP plus one length point for the fifth \D. 
That is enough for a 2/1 response so North says 2\D.
The partnership is now forced to reach game so South bids 2NT. This describes a balanced hand with exactly 5 \Hs and no 4-card \S suit.  What should you bid now?
North is happy to play in Notrump, and with no extra strength above the 13 points already promised, uses Quick Arrival and bids 3NT. South passes and a reasonable game contract is reached.
Notice that you would bid this hand the same way whether or not you play 2/1.
}

